EverTools Beta Release 6 distribution files are now avalible on the file download page.  All current users of EverMon will need to manually update evermon in order to get to the latest version.  If you already are using EverTools, then you should download the small (Update) file.<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>1:30pm - Update Errors</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
There was a new update to EverMon/EverChat that was posted around 11:30am EST today.  Anyone that downloaded that update between then and 12:30pm will notice that EverMon/EverChat/Control Center no longer will function as a result to a major bug in the software.  This will require a manual patch update which I will post as soon as I have the bug fixed.<BR><BR>
In the mean time, I've turned off all Auto-Update support.  When you try to auto-update you will get a message saying that your version is too old to auto-update.  I will post more info on the needed fix later.<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Wednesday, February 9th, 2000</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>9:25am - New Download Site</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
I would like to thank the guys at <a href='http://www.danbo.com/EverQuest'>The Barbarian's Domain</a> for also becoming
a distribution site for EverTools.  If you play a barbarian, you will definatly
want to check their site out!<br><br>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Tuesday, January 25th, 2000</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>3:20pm - Suggestions forum added</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
Now that EverTools is in beta, I've added another public message base area
called 'Suggestions'.  You can find this under the 'Message Boards' option
on the menu to the left.  Please feel free to use this board to place any
and all ideas for additions or updates to current or future Evertool utilities.<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>2:30pm - Install File Problems</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
A small problem was found in the first set of EverTools beta install files.
If you downloaded evertools_5_beta_lg.exe or evertools_5_beta_sm.exe before
2:30pm EST today, and if you are having setup or install problems, you might
want to re-download them again to get the updated install versions.  Sorry
for any problems this has caused.<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>11:30am - EverTools Beta Officially Released</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
It's finally here! Beginning today, EverTools, along with the newly enhanced
EverMon 3.0, is now officially being released as a public open-beta.  Click
on the download menu option to the left of the screen to learn more on how
you can download EverTools Beta.<br><br>

Remember, EverTools, and the new EverMon 3.0 which is included with EverTools,
replaces the old EverMon 2.1, as well as the old Uninet Launcher software.
If you are using the old version of EverMon, you might wish to consider
downloading the EverTools beta version.<br><br>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Monday, January 24th, 2000</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>3:00pm - EQCharInfo and EverTools join forces</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
Effective immediately, Jason Blood, author and developer of the popular
EQCharInfo Everquest Log Parser software, has joined up with the EverTools
development team.  Jason's EQCharInfo software will now become the new
EverLogs component of EverTools.  Jason will still retain full rights to
the software, as well as be responsible for the continued updates and
upgrades to the software.  The new EverLogs will still be upgraded via
EverTool's auto-updater, just like all the other EverTools software<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Wednesday, January 5th, 2000</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>3:30pm - Links Updated</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
Some of the links on the menu on the left of the page were no working, They
should be working now.  Also, until there is a Beta version of EverTools to
download, the EverTools download link will point to the old EverMon/Launcher
download instructions.<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Tuesday, January 4th, 2000</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>4:30pm - EverTools Alphas released</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
I've started to release alpha versions of a few of the EverTool utilities to those that are on the EverTools development list.  The first one I've released is EverLog (Log File Parser) tomarrow EverMon 3.0 alpha will be relased.<BR><BR>
<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>04:15pm - New Message Board area added</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>
